    "body": "The starship notification features is intentionally barebones because what you're asking for (a full-featured terminal notification daemon) requires coordination of the graphical display server, the shell, and the notification daemon. \r\n\r\nIf you want a full-featured notification system, I recommend finding one written specifically for your shell and disabling the one in starship. For instance, fish has [fish-done](https://github.com/franciscolourenco/done) (which I use on several of my systems) which supports all the features you're looking for and more.",
